<br>
Does it reflect how that person roleplays with their friends, you, other ppl who you do not know and frankly may never know here?  <br>
<br>
Do you even know that person with an_apparent_offensive_name_01 and how she/he roleplays their character?  <br>
<br>
Why does everyone get heated when they see an offensive name(from what they determine to be from their own opinion) to the &quot;character of the server&quot; and think how much of a better place it would be without that person when you (I'll bet my salary that you) don't even know them?<br>
<br>
Personally, I roleplay.  Not 100% all the time nope, but I do a good share.  I have this good/evil thing going on with an old friend from another life, I rp with some guildmates, and with my woman!  That's my game and it's none of your damn business, but if you care to know look me up in game(excellent human/elvish, average dwarvish, feeble halfling/gnomish) and we'll chat about it.  To other people, they have their own game.  Leave them alone for god's sakes.<br>
<br>
Thought for the day:  Assumptions are the mother of all @#%$-ups. (sry jaxy I'm being bad)....ie.. don't assume just b/c someone has an &quot;objective&quot; name that they aren't rp'ing, b/c isn't that what this is all about anyways, rp'ing?  Or is it just a gripe about names, which, well, hehe, there's other things to worry about my little friends.... like the wrath of my hammer and sword coming down upon you...<br>
